.TH diodexp 8 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
diodexp \- list diod exports
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdiodexp\fR \fI[-a key] host\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B diodexp
lists file systems exported by the distributed I/O daemon, which is an I/O
forwarding service for Linux clusters.
.LP
In addition, \fBdiodexp\fR can be used to implement an \fBautofs\fR program
map for purposes of making \fBdiod\fR mounts available on demand with
minimal client configuration.
.SH OPTIONS
With no options, \fBdiodexp\fR lists the export paths.
.TP
.I "-a, --auto-indirect KEY"
Look up KEY and return corresponding indirect map entry, if any.
Keys are either the basename of a server export path or the full path with
hyphens as separators and no leading separator.  Example:
server export `/usr/local', keys are `local' or `usr-local'.
In the event that keys are not unique, the first one in the export list
will be returned.
.SH "FILES"
/etc/auto.diod
.SH "SEE ALSO"
diod (8),
diodctl (8),
diodctl.conf (5)
